---
import FaqAccordion from '@/components/FaqAccordion.astro'
---

<FaqAccordion
  heading="Frequently asked questions"
  items={[
    {
      question: "Does dermaplaning hurt?",
      answer_html: "<p>No. Dermaplaning is a gentle, painless procedure. You may feel a light scratching sensation as the blade glides across the skin, but most clients find it very comfortable. There is no pain, redness, or discomfort during the treatment.</p>"
    },
    {
      question: "Will my hair grow back thicker or darker?",
      answer_html: "<p>No, this is one of the most common misconceptions about dermaplaning. The fine vellus hair (peach fuzz) that is removed grows back at the same rate, texture, and color as before. Dermaplaning does not affect the hair follicle at all.</p>"
    },
    {
      question: "Is there any downtime after dermaplaning?",
      answer_html: "<p>None. You can return to your normal activities immediately after your dermaplaning facial. Your skin may look slightly flushed for an hour or two, but there is no peeling, swelling, or recovery period required.</p>"
    },
    {
      question: "Who is a good candidate for dermaplaning?",
      answer_html: "<p>Dermaplaning is safe for most skin types, including sensitive skin. It is particularly beneficial for those with dry skin, dull complexion, fine lines, or uneven texture. We do not recommend it for active acne breakouts or certain skin conditions, your esthetician will assess your skin during the consultation.</p>"
    },
  ]}
/>
